[h2 
	"Game Controls
	$LF
	[a id=heading-280 
	]a
]h2
[h3 
	"Control Scheme
	$LF
	[a id=heading-296 
	]a
]h3
[ul 
	[li 
		[b 
			"A
		]b
		"	-	Special Attack
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		[b 
			"B
		]b
		"	-	Jump
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		[b 
			"X
		]b
		"	-	Weapon Change (Forward)
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		[b 
			"Y
		]b
		"	-	Attack
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		[b 
			"L
		]b
		"	-	Tumble
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		[b 
			"R
		]b
		"	-	Tumble
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		[b 
			"SELECT
		]b
		"	-	Weapon Change (Backward)
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		[b 
			"START
		]b
		"	-	Pause
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[hr 
]hr
[h3 
	"Jump
	$LF
	[a id=heading-495 
	]a
]h3
[p 
	"Just like any other game, Hagane jumps by holding 
	[b 
		"B
	]b
	". While jumping tapping 
	[b 
		"B
	]b
	" and then holding it makes Hagane perform a spin jump. 
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"When falling you can hold 
	[b 
		"Down
	]b
	" on the control pad to flame kick, does 1 damage and when it collides with an object (enemies, projectiles or background objects) Hagane bounces after the attack and gets a little height.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"On the ground if you hold 
	[b 
		"Down
	]b
	" and then 
	[b 
		"B
	]b
	" Hagane slides. Usable on slopes only when going down.
	$LF
]p
[hr 
]hr
[h3 
	"Special Attack
	$LF
	[a id=heading-975 
	]a
]h3
[p 
	"An explosion that covers the entire screen and damages all enemies within it.  Uses 1 bomb charge.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Deals 6 damage over 53 frames at 2 damage per hit. Adds 26 lag frames.
	$LF
]p
[hr 
]hr
[h3 
	"Weapons
	$LF
	[a id=heading-1168 
	]a
]h3
[p 
	"Hagane has access to 4 different weapons that you use with 
	[b 
		"Y
	]b
	":
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		[b 
			"Sword
		]b
		": Melee attack. 2 damage.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		[b 
			"Kunai
		]b
		": Projectile. Flies in a straight line, 2 damage. Only 2 projectiles from Hagane can be on the screen at the same time.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		[b 
			"Bomb
		]b
		": Projectile. Flies in an arc, direct contact does 2 damage while the explosion that results from it does 1 damage. Only 2 projectiles from Hagane can be on the screen at the same time.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		[b 
			"Chain
		]b
		": Semi Ranged attack. Flies in a straight line, extends to a certain limit and then retracts doing 1 damage. If holding UP on the control pad, launches the chain upwards and if it hits the ceiling can bring Hagane towards it.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[p 
	"You can change weapons using the 
	[b 
		"X
	]b
	" to scroll forward or 
	[b 
		"SELECT
	]b
	" to scroll backwards, takes 1 frame.
	$LF
]p
[hr 
]hr
[h3 
	"Tumble
	$LF
	[a id=heading-1953 
	]a
]h3
[p 
	"Tumbling is a special action that behaves according to the direction Hagane is facing. 
	[b 
		"L
	]b
	" tumbles to the left. 
	[b 
		"R
	]b
	" tumbles to the right.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"If you tumble forward Hagane enters a flashing animation that has 3 phases. After each phase you can use either 
	[b 
		"Y
	]b
	" or 
	[b 
		"B
	]b
	" to do a special attack.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[b 
		"Phase 1
	]b
	": Hagane rolls forward.
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		[b 
			"Y
		]b
		": Slides forward with the sword. 
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		[b 
			"B
		]b
		": Jump Kick.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[p 
	[b 
		"Phase 2
	]b
	": After phase 1, Hagane flashes blue and jumps.
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		[b 
			"Y
		]b
		": Somersault Kick.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		[b 
			"B
		]b
		": Spinning Kick. Hits multiple times.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[p 
	[b 
		"Phase 3
	]b
	": After phase 2, Hagane flashes yellow and jumps higher.
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		[b 
			"Y
		]b
		": Slams his sword into the ground releasing a fire dragon that spreads out and does damage to all enemies nearby.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		[b 
			"B
		]b
		": Vertical Kick. 25 damage.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[p 
	"If you tumble backwards, Hagane back flips and gains invincibility through it's duration.
	$LF
]p
[hr 
]hr
[h2 
	"Tricks
	$LF
	[a id=heading-2800 
	]a
]h2
[h3 
	"Camera Manipulation
	$LF
	[a id=heading-2809 
	]a
]h3
[p 
	"Reaching a certain point in some stages triggers a cut-scene, boss fight or an end level flag. Some of these points are triggered by camera position instead of Hagane sprite. Spin-jumping, backflipping or slidding DOESN'T move the camera. Standing still, walking and tumbling forwards do. Walking is quicker in cases when Hagane is on the edge of the screen.
	$LF
]p
[h3 
	"Animation Canceling
	$LF
	[a id=heading-3191 
	]a
]h3
[p 
	"Every ground attack from Hagane can be canceled 1 frame after executing it, this allows Hagane to inmediately launch another one.
	$LF
	"To perfom this just slide 
	"[__Down__+__B__]
	" for 1 frame after perfoming an action.
	$LF
]p
[h3 
	"Vertical Boost
	$LF
	[a id=heading-3426 
	]a
]h3
[p 
	"If you input a Flame Kick 
	(__wikiLink|__Down__ in the air)
	" and collide with an object (enemies, projectiles or background objects) Hagane bounces after the attack and gets a little height. This height can be dramatically improved by pressing and holding 
	(__wikiLink|__B__)
	" before the collision, in cases where the object is to close to Hagane leave an empty frame and then input 
	"[__Down__+__B__]
	".
	$LF
]p
[h3 
	"Chain Glitch
	$LF
	[a id=heading-3819 
	]a
]h3
[p 
	"The chain glitch allows Hagane to enter certain walls and climb them incredibly fast. To perform it follow these instructions:
	$LF
]p
[ol 
	[li 
		" Place Hagane facing away from the wall.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Jump and attack with the chain.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Press and hold towards the wall for 10-11 frames. This will force the Hagane sprite inside the wall.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Press 
		[b 
			"Down
		]b
		". Hagane will do a Flame Kick, and then switch to a crouching state.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Jump again and repeat.
		$LF
	]li
]ol
[p 
	"If the sprite is by the edge of the wall Hagane will zip inside it, killing him if he goes too deep. To avoid this, just throw a projectile so Hagane can rise to the level of the platform.
	$LF
]p
